

4
00:00:39,127 --> 00:00:40,664
<i>Mist coming in--</i>

5
00:00:42,243 --> 00:00:48,454
<i>--Like something is brewing,
about to begin--</i>

6
00:00:48,654 --> 00:00:53,609
<i>--Can't put me finger on what lies in store--</i>

7
00:00:54,309 --> 00:01:00,252
<i>--But I feel what's to happen,
all happened before--</i>

8
00:01:38,058 --> 00:01:39,079
Mrs Travers.

9
00:01:45,933 --> 00:01:47,471
Like pink clouds on sticks.

10
00:01:48,877 --> 00:01:49,811
Excuse me?

11
00:01:50,144 --> 00:01:54,454
The cherry blossoms,
I was trying to think of what it looks like--

12
00:01:55,618 --> 00:01:56,534
The car should be here, by now.

13
00:01:56,839 --> 00:01:58,533
May I use.. the phone?

14
00:01:59,265 --> 00:02:03,440
I cancelled it.
- You--?  What?

15
00:02:05,908 --> 00:02:08,202
Pamela!
- Mrs Travers.

16
00:02:08,402 --> 00:02:09,402
Mrs Travers...

17
00:02:09,668 --> 00:02:12,160
Why would you cancel the car?
- I shan't be going.

18
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,872
We've been through this.

19
00:02:15,072 --> 00:02:18,247
- I've changed my mind.
- You made an agreement.

20
00:02:18,447 --> 00:02:21,040
Do you understand?
A verbal agreement.

21
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:23,273
Why in the world are you speaking to me
as if I am a neonate?

22
00:02:23,473 --> 00:02:26,053
He's going to--
- What? What is he going to do? Sue?

23
00:02:26,253 --> 00:02:28,715
He is very welcome to every penny
I don't posess.

24
00:02:28,915 --> 00:02:33,674
Look----I've represented you for a long time.

25
00:02:34,546 --> 00:02:36,885
I like to think of you as a friend--

26
00:02:38,038 --> 00:02:40,629
I like to think of it,
believe me I know it's not reciprocated.

27
00:02:41,863 --> 00:02:42,948
I would never,

28
00:02:43,504 --> 00:02:46,544
suggest you do something that would cause you
anguish but there's no more money Pamela

29
00:02:47,833 --> 00:02:50,173
-- Mrs Travers. Simply no more.

30
00:02:50,633 --> 00:02:54,255
Sales have dried up, no more royalties.
You refuse to write further books so-

31
00:02:57,382 --> 00:02:58,764
Do you understand? I'm..

32
00:02:59,456 --> 00:03:01,100
I'm..frightened,
you don't understand what that means.

33
00:03:01,984 --> 00:03:03,730
I know what he's going to do to her--

34
00:03:03,930 --> 00:03:07,916
- she'll be cavorting and twinkling!
Careening towards a happy ending like a kamikaze--

35
00:03:08,229 --> 00:03:09,833
--We've been trying to do this deal for twenty years!

36
00:03:10,414 --> 00:03:12,359
He's agreed to both your stipulations.
No animation,

37
00:03:12,991 --> 00:03:15,490
script approval--
- Use her to pay my bills? If I believed..

38
00:03:15,491 --> 00:03:17,990
in a hell I'll be sitting in its waiting room--

39
00:03:17,991 --> 00:03:22,610
--script approval! He's never granted
anything like that before! I don't know what else to do!

40
00:03:29,549 --> 00:03:32,521
Where is Polly?
- I fired her.

41
00:03:33,942 --> 00:03:37,503
It's just as well. It seems
I can't afford her anymore anyway.

42
00:03:42,557 --> 00:03:44,558
You don't know how much she means to me.

43
00:03:44,758 --> 00:03:45,758
Polly?

44
00:03:46,134 --> 00:03:47,709
Of course not Polly!

45
00:03:47,909 --> 00:03:53,467
For God's sake.
Los...Angeles.

46
00:03:56,469 --> 00:03:58,175
You have only to go there and work for two weeks.

47
00:03:59,654 --> 00:04:00,583
Collaborate.

48
00:04:01,850 --> 00:04:03,854
You haven't signed the rights over, yet.
- Yet!

49
00:04:04,446 --> 00:04:06,357
You must make it work Mrs Travers--
- Oh I must, must I?

50
00:04:07,172 --> 00:04:11,289
You need the money. I don't want you to see you--
- Stop saying money! It's a filthy, disgusting word!

51
00:04:11,489 --> 00:04:13,090
I am picking up the telephone Mrs Travers--

52
00:04:20,756 --> 00:04:21,664
I..I have final say?
- You do.

53
00:04:22,736 --> 00:04:24,314
I have final say.

54
00:04:25,085 --> 00:04:26,851
And if I don't like what they are doing to her?

55
00:04:27,516 --> 00:04:28,651
Then, You don't sign the papers.

56
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,860
He cannot make the film unless
you grant the rights.

57
00:04:33,958 --> 00:04:36,427
It's an exploratory trip--

58
00:04:38,648 --> 00:04:40,984
What do you say?

59
00:04:43,716 --> 00:04:46,770
I want to keep my house.

60
00:04:58,172 --> 00:04:59,495
mm..hhm?
Excuse me ma'am,

61
00:04:59,965 --> 00:05:01,817
have you seen my daughter?

62
00:05:02,664 --> 00:05:06,324
I was quite sure,
I had left her around here somewhere!

63
00:05:06,524 --> 00:05:09,302
Her name is Helen,

64
00:05:09,502 --> 00:05:10,502
no, erm.. Shirley,

65
00:05:11,218 --> 00:05:17,690
No, erm.. good lord;
I've quite forgotten!

66
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:20,372
Could it be Prunella?
- No!

67
00:05:21,570 --> 00:05:22,892
Pamela?
- No, no...no. No!

68
00:05:24,605 --> 00:05:27,226
I'm sure I have a special name for her..
- Ginty!

69
00:05:27,791 --> 00:05:29,750
Why, thank you ma'am!
Ginty it is of course!

70
00:05:31,434 --> 00:05:33,484
Now, have you seen her?
- It's me!

71
00:05:39,735 --> 00:05:40,721
Gosh! So it is!

72
00:05:41,643 --> 00:05:43,088
Well, thank goodness for that!

73
00:05:44,784 --> 00:05:46,744
I was positive, I was going to be beheaded for losing..

74
00:05:47,476 --> 00:05:52,934
Her Highness.. The Royal Princess
Ginty Mc Featherfluffy!

75
00:05:53,134 --> 00:05:54,134
You can't lose me!

76
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,273
Never. I promise.

77
00:05:58,207 --> 00:05:59,998
I will never lose you!

78
00:06:00,198 --> 00:06:02,176
You ready?
Are you sure?

79
00:06:02,376 --> 00:06:05,500
C'mon! The adventure is about to begin!
C'mon.

80
00:06:06,036 --> 00:06:08,535
Line: 84   (Silen=83.62) (EMedp=1.985)

81
00:06:08,536 --> 00:06:12,425
Line: 85   (Silen=80.21) (EMedp=2.171)

82
00:06:18,418 --> 00:06:21,474
Can I help you?
- I'm perfectly capable thank you.

83
00:06:21,674 --> 00:06:22,674
They've used all the space;

84
00:06:22,874 --> 00:06:25,810
...so greedy.
- I'll take it Madam.  I can put it up in front.

85
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:27,010
I don't want it up there. I would it here,

86
00:06:27,210 --> 00:06:29,675
in the corresponding holding area
for my assigned seat!

87
00:06:29,875 --> 00:06:32,695
The flight's closing in just a few moments Madam.
I'll have to take it.

88
00:06:32,895 --> 00:06:36,152
You can move mine instead.
It's the grey one.

89
00:06:36,352 --> 00:06:37,352
- Thank you.

90
00:06:44,651 --> 00:06:47,854
Will the child be a nuisance?
It's an eleven hour flight.

91
00:06:50,801 --> 00:06:53,496
Er-- no,--
- Jolly good.

92
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:04,224
I hope we crash.

93
00:07:08,135 --> 00:07:09,613
Where is he carriage?

94
00:07:10,534 --> 00:07:11,477
A carriage? Who needs a carriage?

95
00:07:12,743 --> 00:07:15,571
But, there's so many...
- Every leisurely stroll is a gift, Darling!

96
00:07:15,771 --> 00:07:16,771
It's a gift!

97
00:07:18,173 --> 00:07:20,373
Now, Biddy..
are up staying?

98
00:07:20,573 --> 00:07:21,573
You're coming with us?
- Mmm, hm.

99
00:07:21,773 --> 00:07:22,773
Excellent!

100
00:07:26,310 --> 00:07:30,528
Thank you so much.
For everything.<font color=#D3EFFE>-: D</font>

101
00:07:30,728 --> 00:07:31,728
Thank you, Miss.

102
00:07:32,717 --> 00:07:35,422
Hurry up, everyone!
We mustn't be late the train.

103
00:07:36,924 --> 00:07:39,320
All aboard!
Everybody ready?

104
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:40,520
Yes.

105
00:07:41,528 --> 00:07:44,069
See you soon Katie Nanna!
- Take care, love.

106
00:07:45,644 --> 00:07:47,184
Everybody ready?

107
00:07:49,168 --> 00:07:51,912
Walking bus!
Left, right..left...

108
00:07:52,112 --> 00:07:53,112
Miss?

109
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:58,049
Thank you.

110
00:08:08,810 --> 00:08:11,309
Left. Left, right left...

111
00:08:11,310 --> 00:08:13,809
And, one, two three-
New town,

112
00:08:13,810 --> 00:08:16,994
new job, new bank.
New life.

113
00:08:17,519 --> 00:08:20,658
Come on, my little ducklings!

114
00:08:21,230 --> 00:08:26,240
Left, right left..
C'mon, come along!

115
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:35,890
Hold!

116
00:08:57,662 --> 00:08:58,520
Allora--

117
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:01,295
Ginty, Come on, my love.

118
00:09:55,179 --> 00:09:58,163
<font color=#50BEFA>Pilot:</font><i>"Ladies and Gentlemen,
we begin our descent into Los Angeles."</i>

119
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:25,365
Fiery dust, I see.

120
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:29,105
Travers? P.L. Travers?
- Mrs.

121
00:10:30,290 --> 00:10:32,060
Welcome, Mrs P.L. Travers!
Welcome to the City of Angels.

122
00:10:32,820 --> 00:10:34,150
Let me take those.

123
00:10:35,060 --> 00:10:37,575
I'm perfectly capable of-- Oh, nevermind.

124
00:10:44,735 --> 00:10:46,475
Sun came out to say hello just to you.

125
00:10:46,675 --> 00:10:48,995
Don't be preposterous.

126
00:10:49,780 --> 00:10:50,805
It smells. Like--

127
00:10:51,265 --> 00:10:55,327
Jasmine.
--chlorine and sweat.

128
00:10:55,527 --> 00:10:57,406
It's dreadful.

129
00:11:21,049 --> 00:11:22,560
Absurt.

130
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:24,655
You okay back there Mrs P.L. Travers?

131
00:11:25,535 --> 00:11:30,810
It's not Mrs P.L. It's just Mrs--
Oh, it's too hot.

132
00:11:31,230 --> 00:11:32,670
No problemo!

133
00:11:33,285 --> 00:11:36,770
No problemo! We got a brand new
air conditioning system, Missus;

134
00:11:39,435 --> 00:11:42,370
Just about make you feel like
you're in good old Engerland again!

135
00:11:42,570 --> 00:11:45,673
Things they can put in cars these days--

136
00:11:45,873 --> 00:11:46,873
Gosh almighty.

137
00:11:49,076 --> 00:11:51,299
No problemo.

138
00:12:06,553 --> 00:12:08,465
And, here we are. Ma'm.

139
00:12:13,328 --> 00:12:14,239
Thank you.
- Ma'am?

140
00:12:14,736 --> 00:12:17,202
Would you like me to unpack for you ma'am?

141
00:12:18,699 --> 00:12:21,499
Young man, if it is your wish to handle ladies garments;

142
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:24,514
May I suggest, you take employment in a launderette.

143
00:12:26,904 --> 00:12:28,496
Odd.

144
00:12:36,469 --> 00:12:38,540
Oh, Dear.

145
00:12:38,740 --> 00:12:39,740
For Heaven's sake...

146
00:12:40,566 --> 00:12:41,944
What on earth..

147
00:12:54,063 --> 00:12:55,635
Oh no, no, no.
No, no, no.

148
00:12:55,835 --> 00:12:56,835
This will never do.

149
00:12:57,117 --> 00:12:58,178
Absolutely, no pears.

150
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:01,539
No pears.

151
00:13:14,814 --> 00:13:15,730
A palace!

152
00:13:15,930 --> 00:13:18,887
Complete with mighty steed.

153
00:13:19,087 --> 00:13:20,797
And chickens.

154
00:13:20,997 --> 00:13:21,997
Oh, my..

155
00:13:22,896 --> 00:13:24,082
We'll build beautiful memories here my angel.

156
00:13:27,508 --> 00:13:28,813
Girls, come on.

157
00:13:31,838 --> 00:13:36,983
--in this house, you get to share room.

158
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,576
How old do you think i am?

159
00:14:14,202 --> 00:14:19,445
A five years old...
I suppose.

160
00:14:51,294 --> 00:14:55,248
And you can stay there
until you learn the art of subtlety.

161
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:23,339
There you are.

162
00:15:24,281 --> 00:15:25,151
Don't worry!

163
00:15:25,597 --> 00:15:27,706
There's nothing wrong with your television set.

164
00:15:27,906 --> 00:15:29,000
This is a pixie bell,

165
00:15:29,705 --> 00:15:31,273
the sound is much too high for human ears.

166
00:15:32,966 --> 00:15:35,511
Oh, there you are Tink!

167
00:15:37,025 --> 00:15:38,912
Hey! What..Hey!

168
00:15:39,654 --> 00:15:41,914
Get that stuff off of me!

169
00:15:43,207 --> 00:15:45,619
You know, if you're familiar with our story
of Peter Pan.

170
00:15:46,405 --> 00:15:48,917
You know, a little sprinkling of fairy dust
can make you fly!

171
00:15:51,172 --> 00:15:53,885
Where are you going, Tink?
Haven't you forgotten something?

172
00:15:54,085 --> 00:15:55,085
Off!

173
00:15:55,522 --> 00:15:58,235
That's how we deal with you.

174
00:16:14,185 --> 00:16:16,760
Good morning Mrs!
- It's not Mrs, it's-- Oh, nevermind.

175
00:16:18,604 --> 00:16:20,242
We're just not going to get it right are we?

176
00:16:20,575 --> 00:16:21,820
What's that?

177
00:16:22,460 --> 00:16:23,574
Will it be the same..

178
00:16:24,057 --> 00:16:28,072
driver every day?
- Yes ma'am! I'm all yours.

179
00:16:30,183 --> 00:16:31,555
Hey, Sun came out again!

180
00:16:32,741 --> 00:16:36,379
You say it like you're surprised.
As if the sun is particular about whom it appears.

181
00:16:36,834 --> 00:16:40,179
It seems you think that I am responsible,
for it's miraculous dawning every day.

182
00:16:40,379 --> 00:16:42,466
For heaven's sake, it's California!

183
00:16:42,666 --> 00:16:43,666
It certainly is!

184
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:53,240
I would so much rather be accountable for the rain.

185
00:16:53,550 --> 00:16:55,150
Oh, that's sad.

186
00:16:55,470 --> 00:16:57,060
Sad is entirely the wrong emotion.

187
00:16:57,870 --> 00:17:00,180
I shan't bother explaining why;
it'll just...Zip!

188
00:17:01,490 --> 00:17:02,590
Okey dokey.

189
00:17:04,980 --> 00:17:06,660
The rain brings life!

190
00:17:10,344 --> 00:17:12,035
So does the sun.

191
00:17:13,089 --> 00:17:15,314
Be quiet!
- Yes ma'am.

192
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:38,165
I'll get that, Sir!

193
00:17:39,090 --> 00:17:40,400
Got it?
- Yes, sir.

194
00:17:44,740 --> 00:17:46,650
Good morning! Pamela!

195
00:17:47,170 --> 00:17:51,030
It is so discomfiting to hear a perfect stranger
use my first name.

196
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:53,705
Mrs Travers. Please.

197
00:17:53,905 --> 00:17:54,905
I do apologize,

198
00:17:55,105 --> 00:17:59,567
Mrs Travers.
I am Don DaGradi, the script writer.

199
00:17:59,767 --> 00:18:03,376
Co-script-writer.
I shall certainly be having my say Mr. DiGraydi.

200
00:18:03,576 --> 00:18:04,576
Gradi.

201
00:18:05,420 --> 00:18:10,267
Wonderful! I welcome your input.
- If indeed we ever sign off on a script.

202
00:18:10,467 --> 00:18:11,540
Right, uhmm..

203
00:18:12,790 --> 00:18:17,081
this is the rest of your team,
This is Dick and Bob Sherman! Music and lyrics.

204
00:18:17,281 --> 00:18:21,406
Boys, this is the one and only Mrs P.L. Travers,
creator of our beloved Mary.

205
00:18:21,890 --> 00:18:23,761
Poppins.
<i>- Who else?</i> - Mary Poppins.

206
00:18:23,961 --> 00:18:24,961
Never ever, just Mary.

207
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:29,841
A pleasure to meet you, though I  fear
we shan't be acquainted for too long.

208
00:18:30,041 --> 00:18:31,041
Why is that?
- B'cos These books...

209
00:18:31,241 --> 00:18:35,506
simply do not lend themselves
to chirping and prancing.

210
00:18:35,890 --> 00:18:36,870
No. Certainly not a musical.

211
00:18:37,730 --> 00:18:39,536
Now, where is Mister Disney?

212
00:18:39,736 --> 00:18:43,396
I should so much like to get this started and finished
as briskly as is humanly possible.

213
00:18:43,596 --> 00:18:46,224
Perhaps, one of you can point me in his direction.
That'd be superb..wonderful. Thank you.

214
00:18:46,424 --> 00:18:47,424
We were hoping to give you
a little tour of the studio.

215
00:18:48,730 --> 00:18:49,620
No thank you.

216
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:52,040
Walt just wants to show the place off.

217
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:53,840
No one likes a show off.

218
00:18:55,185 --> 00:18:56,925
Mrs Travers-- it's quitea long way--

219
00:18:57,490 --> 00:18:58,585
Not a musical?

220
00:19:04,425 --> 00:19:06,695
I am perfectly capable of walking.

221
00:19:17,870 --> 00:19:19,160
Good morning.
- Good morning, Dolly..

222
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:21,200
Could you let Mister Disney know
I have arrived please?

223
00:19:21,930 --> 00:19:22,840
Absolutely, please have a seat.

224
00:19:23,190 --> 00:19:24,580
Oh, no. There's no need.

225
00:19:25,370 --> 00:19:30,390
He'll be just a.. a moment, Mrs.Travers.
Why don't we sit.

226
00:19:38,259 --> 00:19:39,994
She's here!

227
00:19:40,194 --> 00:19:43,292
A word of advice Mrs Travers, if I may.

228
00:19:43,492 --> 00:19:45,940
You may. Whether I heed it or not
will be another matter entirely.

229
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:54,193
Uhm. It's just that he can't stand being called Mr Disney.

230
00:19:54,530 --> 00:19:56,640
We are all on a first name basis here.

231
00:20:02,270 --> 00:20:03,820
Well,

232
00:20:04,260 --> 00:20:06,260
there ya are at last!

233
00:20:07,110 --> 00:20:09,609
Oh, my dear gal!

234
00:20:09,610 --> 00:20:13,550
You can't imagine how excited I am to finally meet you!

235
00:20:14,790 --> 00:20:18,047
Hum-- well, It's an honour, Mister Disney.
- Oh Walt, you gotta call me Walt.

236
00:20:18,247 --> 00:20:20,382
‘Mister Disney?was my old man.
Isn't that right, Don?

237
00:20:20,582 --> 00:20:21,582
Absolutely, Walt.

238
00:20:22,470 --> 00:20:28,080
Tommie, say hello to...
the one and only Pamela Travers!

239
00:20:28,530 --> 00:20:29,930
It's so nice to meet you.

240
00:20:31,470 --> 00:20:36,037
Ya know, I can't believe it. P.L. Travers,
right here, in my office,

241
00:20:36,237 --> 00:20:38,691
after all these years-- almost twenty of ‘em.

242
00:20:39,630 --> 00:20:41,220
Yes.
- Twenty. Long. Years.

243
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:43,530
Wish ya coulda?seen me then Pam!

244
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:47,310
As lean as a whippet I was! A race horse!

245
00:20:47,780 --> 00:20:48,910
Well, anyway...

246
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:50,720
here you are. Look at you!

247
00:20:51,640 --> 00:20:52,770
I could eat you up!

248
00:20:54,490 --> 00:20:55,840
That wouldn't be appropriate.

249
